plot_notes: 15 m from shore, mixed Rhizophora and Avicennia, trees ~ <15ft, no barnacles, brittle brances, healthy leaves
Water ~3 in deep, healthier trees, more spaced out trees, open canopy, mostly Avicennia, no barnacles, healthy leaves

mostly Avicennia, leaves being eaten, open canopy, standing water 3 in, mostly 6-15 ft

30-35ft trees, more open canopy, mixed Rh and Av, insect eaten leaves (but green), oxygen stress, standing water, lots of saplings
tall trees above ~40 ft, mix of Rh and Av with a few La, high standing water 4-6in, healthier leaves, oxygen stress
tall trees above ~40 ft, mostly Av with a few La, high standing water 4-6in, healthier leaves, oxygen stress
mix of Rh, Av, La, up to >40 ft tall, lots of saplings, high standing water 2-4 in, healthier leaves

mostly Rh, standing water 5 in, deep water color with lighter brown soft sediment
tall La 25-30 ft, sediment has a little fungi, standing water 2 in, light brown water
Av, surface water 3 in, 25 ft tall trees

all red mangrove, low canopy, 3 in of water
red mangrove, dwarf, 5 in standing water light in color

dwarf patchy red mangrove, 6 in standing water
high tide, dwarf red & black mid, ankle deep water, algae on surface of sediments around 3-4mm
denser red mangrove, lots of saplings, ankle deep water
mix of red and black, less dense area (sparse), ankle deep water
sparse red and black mangrove, ankle deep water, algae on surface sediments
sparse red and black mangrove, ankle deep water, lots of curved roots on red (hurricane?)
very sparse mangrove, red (60%) and black (40%) mix
forest mix of palms/marsh shrubs/mangroves, muddy with small pockests of water
sparse red mangrove, bromeliad and shrubs, standing water 6 in
elevated, mostly palms and coconuts, no mangroves
open canopy, mostly palm, no standing water, lots of palm leaves on the ground

moved down river 20-30 m to find more mangroves, 75 cm core = rich peat
15m from edge, huge red mangroves, water over 50% dense red mangrove root, 10cm standing water
sparse canopy of black mangrove, low to medium stature, number of dead or dying trees, standing water approx 6 in, water is warm

sparse mangrove, healthier than previous site, mostly living tree 50% leaf cover, soil firm under foot, algae covering 3mm
emerging from area of mostly dead trees, semi sparse, healthy looking mangroves, 20-25ft tall, firm under foot, water depth 3in, lots of saplings
in the edge of degraded mangrove stand (healthy to the right degraded to the left), black mangrove 20-25ft tall, most 10ft, on degraded side the dead were ~15ft tall

white mangroves, undergrowth, water 6in deep, lots of microplastics

denser mangroves, moslty black about 15-20ft tall, standing water
tall black mangroves, some red mixed in, standing water 4 in
many thin white mangroves with some ery large 30ft tall black mangrove trees, standing water, some red mixed in
end of caye facing orcean, sparse black mangrove with fringing red to the edge, standing water, black trees very large, disturbed area
